   <body>
      <context>
         <p>Follow this procedure to remove the floor burners:</p>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <note id="note_z1t_nfz_5cc">
               <table id="table_h43_4fz_5cc">
                  <tgroup cols="2">
                     <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*"/>
                     <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*"/>
                     <tbody>
                        <row>
                           <entry/>
                           <entry>
                              <p>Lockout tagout.</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </note>
            <p>Close and lockout tagout all the valves on the combustion safety skid and nitrogen
               skid.</p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>Follow plant requirements for lockout tagout.  </li>
               </ul>
               <p>
                  <fig id="fig_ul3_wfz_5cc">
                     <image href="media/image1.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_vl3_wfz_5cc"
                            align="center"/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Shut off the individual burner gas and oxygen valves on all three burner control skids.</p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>The gas and oxygen lines are automatically purged when the burner is turned off.</li>
               </ul>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In DFC, go to the Melter Cooling H3C screen and click the <uicontrol>Burner
                  Skid</uicontrol> tab.</p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>Click the <uicontrol>BNRx-WTR-FL</uicontrol> button.</li>
                  <li>Click the <uicontrol>Alarming</uicontrol> tab.</li>
                  <li>Check the <uicontrol>Shelved</uicontrol> checkbox to disable the burner
                     cooling water alarm.</li>
               </ul>
               <p>
                  <fig id="fig_l2k_lgz_5cc">
                     <image href="media/image2.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_m2k_lgz_5cc"
                            align="center"/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </p>
            <ol id="substeps_ft1_cgz_5cc">
               <li>
                  <p>Turn off the burner cooling water booster pumps at the local
                     disconnects.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Shut off the individual burner cooling water supply and return valves that
                     are located underneath the melter.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <note id="note_ujg_ngz_5cc">
               <table id="table_vjg_ngz_5cc">
                  <tgroup cols="3">
                     <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*"/>
                     <colspec colname="newCol2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*"/>
                     <colspec colname="c2" colnum="3" colwidth="1*"/>
                     <tbody>
                        <row>
                           <entry/>
                           <entry/>
                           <entry/>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry/>
                           <entry/>
                           <entry/>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
               <p>PPE Required: Cut resistant gloves.</p>
               <p>Tools Required: Socket wrench, bucket</p>
            </note>
            <p/>
            <ol id="substeps_itj_qgz_5cc">
               <li>
                  <p>Remove the gas, oxygen, and cooling water lines from the burner.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ul id="ul_rwp_sgz_5cc">
                        <li>Pull each loop to release the safety latches.</li>
                        <li>Insert a blank into each line to prevent debris from entering. </li>
                     </ul>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_iht_wgz_5cc">
                           <image href="media/image3.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_jht_wgz_5cc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <note id="note_dt5_ygz_5cc">
                     <table id="table_et5_ygz_5cc">
                        <tgroup cols="2">
                           <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*"/>
                           <colspec colname="newCol2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*"/>
                           <tbody>
                              <row>
                                 <entry/>
                                 <entry>
                                    <p>Caution: Burners are heavy. </p>
                                 </entry>
                              </row>
                           </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                     </table>
                  </note>
                  <p>Remove the 4 bolts securing each burner.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ul id="ul_ntb_fhz_5cc">
                        <li>Maintain upward pressure so that the burner does not fall.</li>
                        <li>Carefully lower the burner, and place the burner in a safe space.</li>
                        <li>If the burner is stuck, two jackbolts can be installed to push apart the
                           flanges.</li>
                     </ul>
                     <note type="note" id="note_nkc_hhz_5cc">
                        <p>The burner weighs in excess of  9 kg (20 lb ).</p>
                     </note>
                     <ul id="ul_ohb_lhz_5cc">
                        <li>Hold the burner by the stem. </li>
                        <li> Do not hold the burner by the sparger tube. </li>
                     </ul>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_bb1_4hz_5cc">
                           <image href="media/image4.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_cb1_4hz_5cc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Inspect the burner for physical damage and wear.  This includes but is not limited to:</p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>Cracked or dented burners may require replacement.</li>
                  <li>Look for evidence of moisture to find small cracks.</li>
                  <li>Burners with metal contamination must be replaced.</li>
                  <li>Inspect for erosion on the inside and outside of the burner tip.</li>
                  <li>The burner wall thickness is 2.1 mm (0.083 inch).  </li>
               </ul>
               <p>
                  <fig id="fig_xwt_phz_5cc">
                     <image href="media/image5.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_ywt_phz_5cc"
                            align="center"/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <fig id="fig_jgw_qhz_5cc">
                     <image href="media/image6.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_w5r_rhz_5cc"
                            align="center"/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Repeat this procedure for each burner.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
